---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import guideOne from "../assets/guide_one_image_v2.webp";
import landingResponsive from "../assets/publish_as_responsive_landing.png";
import multipleProject from "../assets/multiple_project_landing.png";
import landingCustomDomain from "../assets/landing_custom_domain.png";
import landingPasswordProtection from "../assets/password_protection_landing.png";
import Container from "../components/container.astro";
---

<Layout title="How it works">
  <Container>
    <section class="bg-white pt-8 pb-4 md:pt-14 md:pb-6">
      <div class="text-center mt-14 mb-12">
        <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-6xl font-bold mb-2">How it works</h1>
        <p class="text-base md:text-lg text-slate-600">
          From Figma to live website in 3 simple steps.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="space-y-6 md:space-y-10">
        <div
          class="flex flex-col md:flex-row items-center md:items-center bg-[#F8FAFA] md:max-w-[1007px] min-h-[302px] mx-auto mb-6 rounded-2xl md:rounded-[32px] border border-[#EDEDED] p-4 md:p-8">
          <div class="flex flex-col items-start justify-center flex-1 h-full">
            <div
              class="w-12 h-12 md:w-[62px] md:h-[62px] rounded-full bg-[#4D9F70] text-white flex items-center justify-center text-2xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-4">
              1
            </div>
            <h2
              class="font-semibold text-lg md:text-[24px] md:text-3xl lg:text-2xl mb-2 text-left text-[#2D2B29]">
              Design in figma
            </h2>
            <p
              class="text-base md:text-[18px] text-slate-600 leading-relaxed text-left">
              Skip learning other tools or coding. Bring your entire website or
              portfolio to life right in Figma. Leverage its features like
              transitions, GIFs and video to make it interactive and engaging.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div
            class="flex-shrink-0 mt-4 md:mt-0 md:ml-12 w-full md:w-auto flex justify-center items-center">
            <Image
              src={guideOne}
              alt="Design in Figma"
              class="rounded-xl max-w-full h-auto md:w-[344px] md:h-[205px] object-contain"
            />
          </div>
        </div>
        <div
          class="flex flex-col md:flex-row items-center md:items-center bg-[#F8FAFA] md:max-w-[1007px] min-h-[302px] mx-auto mb-6 rounded-2xl md:rounded-[32px] border border-[#EDEDED] p-4 md:p-8">
          <div class="flex flex-col items-start justify-center flex-1 h-full">
            <div
              class="w-12 h-12 md:w-[62px] md:h-[62px] rounded-full bg-[#4D9F70] text-white flex items-center justify-center text-2xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-4">
              2
            </div>
            <h2
              class="font-semibold text-lg md:text-[24px] md:text-3xl lg:text-2xl mb-2 text-left text-[#2D2B29]">
              Simple setup
            </h2>
            <p
              class="text-base md:text-[18px] text-slate-600 leading-relaxed text-left">
              Sign up and paste in your Figma prototype links for both desktop
              and mobile views ‚Äì this ensures your site works for anyone
              visiting. Preview the site to see your fantastic Figma designs
              brought to life.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div
            class="flex-shrink-0 mt-4 md:mt-0 md:ml-12 w-full md:w-auto flex justify-center items-center">
            <Image
              src={landingResponsive}
              alt="Simple setup"
              class="rounded-xl max-w-full h-auto md:w-[344px] md:h-[205px] object-contain"
            />
          </div>
        </div>
        <div
          class="flex flex-col md:flex-row items-center md:items-center bg-[#F8FAFA] md:max-w-[1007px] min-h-[302px] mx-auto mb-6 rounded-2xl md:rounded-[32px] border border-[#EDEDED] p-4 md:p-8">
          <div class="flex flex-col items-start justify-center flex-1 h-full">
            <div
              class="w-12 h-12 md:w-[62px] md:h-[62px] rounded-full bg-[#4D9F70] text-white flex items-center justify-center text-2xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-4">
              3
            </div>
            <h2
              class="font-semibold text-lg md:text-[24px] md:text-3xl lg:text-2xl mb-2 text-left text-[#2D2B29]">
              Go Live !
            </h2>
            <p
              class="text-base md:text-[18px] text-slate-600 leading-relaxed text-left">
              Publish your site instantly to start securing jobs and clients
              faster. Updates made in Figma are reflected on your site
              instantly. Customize your site with a personalised domain name.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div
            class="flex-shrink-0 mt-4 md:mt-0 md:ml-12 w-full md:w-auto flex justify-center items-center">
            <Image
              src={multipleProject}
              alt="Go Live"
              class="rounded-xl max-w-full h-auto md:w-[344px] md:h-[205px] object-contain"
            />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-20 mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-center mb-2">
        Advanced customization options
      </h2>
      <p class="text-base md:text-lg text-slate-600 text-center mb-8">
        Take your portfolio to the next level with professional features
      </p>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div
          class="bg-white rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 p-8 flex flex-col items-center text-center">
          <div class="text-[91.2px] mb-4">üåê</div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-1">Custom Domain</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-600 mb-2">
            Connect your own domain like yourname.com for professional branding
          </p>
          <a
            href="/features/custom-domain"
            class="text-[#4d9f70] font-medium hover:underline flex items-center gap-1"
            >Learn more <span aria-hidden="true">‚Üí</span></a
          >
        </div>
        <div
          class="bg-white rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 p-8 flex flex-col items-center text-center">
          <div class="text-[91.2px] mb-4">üîí</div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-1">Password Protection</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-600 mb-2">
            Secure confidential work and NDA projects with password access
          </p>
          <a
            href="/features/password-protection"
            class="text-[#4d9f70] font-medium hover:underline flex items-center gap-1"
            >Learn more <span aria-hidden="true">‚Üí</span></a
          >
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-24 mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold text-center mb-12">
        Frequently Asked Questions
      </h2>
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <details
          class="bg-[#F8FAFC] rounded-2xl border border-[#E5EAF0] shadow p-4 md:p-8 mb-6 transition-all duration-300 group"
          open>
          <summary
            class="font-bold text-xl text-[#222] cursor-pointer flex items-center justify-between select-none text-left">
            What Figma features are supported?
            <span
              class="ml-4 transition-transform duration-300 group-open:rotate-180">
              <svg width="28" height="28" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                ><path
                  d="M8 10l4 4 4-4"
                  stroke="#222"
                  stroke-width="2"
                  stroke-linecap="round"
                  stroke-linejoin="round"></path></svg
              >
            </span>
          </summary>
          <div class="mt-4 text-slate-700 text-base leading-relaxed text-left">
            Figmafolio supports all prototype features in Figma, including animations, transitions, scroll behaviors, hover states, and interactive components. You can also use videos, GIFs, and Figma's new responsive prototype features. Whatever works in Figma's prototype preview will work on your published site.
          </div>
        </details>
        <details
          class="bg-[#F8FAFC] rounded-2xl border border-[#E5EAF0] shadow p-4 md:p-8 mb-6 transition-all duration-300 group">
          <summary
            class="font-bold text-xl text-[#222] cursor-pointer flex items-center justify-between select-none text-left">
            How do I get my prototype link from Figma?
            <span
              class="ml-4 transition-transform duration-300 group-open:rotate-180">
              <svg width="28" height="28" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                ><path
                  d="M8 10l4 4 4-4"
                  stroke="#222"
                  stroke-width="2"
                  stroke-linecap="round"
                  stroke-linejoin="round"></path></svg
              >
            </span>
          </summary>
          <div class="mt-4 text-slate-700 text-base leading-relaxed text-left">
            In Figma, click the "Share" button in the top right corner, then select "Copy link" under the prototype tab. Make sure your file's sharing settings allow "Anyone with the link" to view. Paste this link into Figmafolio and you're ready to publish. We recommend having separate prototype links for desktop and mobile views for the best responsive experience.
          </div>
        </details>
        <details
          class="bg-[#F8FAFC] rounded-2xl border border-[#E5EAF0] shadow p-4 md:p-8 mb-6 transition-all duration-300 group">
          <summary
            class="font-bold text-xl text-[#222] cursor-pointer flex items-center justify-between select-none text-left">
            Do changes in Figma update automatically?
            <span
              class="ml-4 transition-transform duration-300 group-open:rotate-180">
              <svg width="28" height="28" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                ><path
                  d="M8 10l4 4 4-4"
                  stroke="#222"
                  stroke-width="2"
                  stroke-linecap="round"
                  stroke-linejoin="round"></path></svg
              >
            </span>
          </summary>
          <div class="mt-4 text-slate-700 text-base leading-relaxed text-left">
            Yes, changes you make in Figma are reflected on your live site automatically. Since Figmafolio embeds your Figma prototype directly, any updates you save in Figma will appear on your published portfolio without needing to republish or update anything in Figmafolio. It's truly a seamless workflow.
          </div>
        </details>
        <details
          class="bg-[#F8FAFC] rounded-2xl border border-[#E5EAF0] shadow p-4 md:p-8 mb-6 transition-all duration-300 group">
          <summary
            class="font-bold text-xl text-[#222] cursor-pointer flex items-center justify-between select-none text-left">
            Can I preview my site before publishing?
            <span
              class="ml-4 transition-transform duration-300 group-open:rotate-180">
              <svg width="28" height="28" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                ><path
                  d="M8 10l4 4 4-4"
                  stroke="#222"
                  stroke-width="2"
                  stroke-linecap="round"
                  stroke-linejoin="round"></path></svg
              >
            </span>
          </summary>
          <div class="mt-4 text-slate-700 text-base leading-relaxed text-left">
            Yes, you can preview exactly how your portfolio will look before making it public. After pasting your prototype links, use the preview feature in your dashboard to see both desktop and mobile views. This lets you verify everything looks right before sharing your portfolio with the world.
          </div>
        </details>
      </div>
    </section>
  </Container>
</Layout>
